    [14]:
    xxxxxxxxxx
     
    #data
    data_path = "RAVDESS"
    [15]:
    xxxxxxxxxx
     
    # FEATURE EXTRACTION FUNCTION
    def extract_features(file_path):
        y, sr = librosa.load(file_path, sr=22050)
        
        # MFCC (13)
        mfcc = librosa.feature.mfcc(y=y, sr=sr, n_mfcc=13)
        mfcc_mean = np.mean(mfcc, axis=1)
        
        # Zero Crossing Rate
        zcr = librosa.feature.zero_crossing_rate(y)
        zcr_mean = np.mean(zcr)
        
        # Spectral Centroid
        spec_centroid = librosa.feature.spectral_centroid(y=y, sr=sr)
        spec_centroid_mean = np.mean(spec_centroid)
        
        # Energy (RMS)
        rms = librosa.feature.rms(y=y)
        rms_mean = np.mean(rms)
        
        # Pitch using autocorrelation
        pitches, magnitudes = librosa.piptrack(y=y, sr=sr)
        pitch = []
        for i in range(pitches.shape[1]):
            index = magnitudes[:, i].argmax()
            pitch.append(pitches[index, i])
        pitch_mean = np.mean([p for p in pitch if p > 0])
        
        # Combine all features
        features = np.hstack([mfcc_mean, zcr_mean, spec_centroid_mean, rms_mean, pitch_mean])
        
        return features
    [18]:
    xxxxxxxxxx
     
    # LOAD DATASET
    for actor in os.listdir(data_path):
        actor_folder = os.path.join(data_path, actor)
        for file in os.listdir(actor_folder):
            if not file.endswith(".wav"):
                continue
            file_path = os.path.join(actor_folder, file)
            parts = file.split("-")
            if len(parts) < 3:
                continue
            emotion = int(parts[2])
            # calm = 2 (normal), angry = 5 (stressed)
            if emotion == 2:
                label = 0
            elif emotion == 5:
                label = 1
            else:
                continue
            features = extract_features(file_path)
            X.append(features)
            y.append(label)
